HEADWORD: Infarce
<hw>In*farce"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>infarcire</ets>: pref. <ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>farcire</ets>,
<ets>fartum</ets> and <ets>farctum</ets>, to stuff, cram.]</ety> <def>To
stuff; to swell.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The body is <qex>infarced</qex> with . . . watery humors.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. Elyot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

